1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:08,000
In centralized live streaming, every viewer pulls the same HLS segments from delivery infrastructure.

2
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:16,000
OpenStreamGrid is an open, platform-independent hybrid P2P-CDN testbed for HLS live streaming.

3
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:25,000
The origin publishes three renditions. A tracker coordinates broadcasts, peers, segments, and live statistics.

4
00:00:25,300 --> 00:00:33,500
Peers cache and verify segments, announce availability, and serve them over WebRTC or HTTP.

5
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:41,000
If a peer is missing, late, or untrusted, the client immediately falls back to the origin.

6
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:49,500
In the real Docker demo, two peers joined, advertised cached segments, and completed peer-to-peer transfers.

7
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:58,500
After disconnecting peers, the same run recorded four origin fallbacks and preserved traffic data through a tracker restart.

8
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:08,500
This local prototype is reproducible, but not a production benchmark. It demonstrates hybrid routing, integrity, and resilience.

9
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:17,200
OpenStreamGrid explores a more distributed and resilient approach to live-stream delivery.
